[{"Id": 1012890, "EnglishTitle": null, "GujaratiTitle": null, "RUrduTitle": null, "UrduTitle": null, "Sequence": 1, "EnglishDescription": "In his book of Zaid al-Ma`ad, Allamah Majlisi, within the recommended acts on the 17th of Rabi-ul-Awwal; the Holy Prophet’s birthday, says that Shaykh Mufid, Shaykh Shahid, and Sayyid Ibn Tawus instructed the following. When you intend to visit the Holy Prophet (s) while you are in any place other than the holy city of Madina, you may perform Ghusl (spiritual bath), stand before something like a grave, write the name of the Holy Prophet (s) on it, concentrate heartily on it, and say the following…", "GujaratiDescription": null, "RUrduDescription": "Allamah Majlisi apni kitaab Zaid al-Ma’ad mein farmaate hai, keh 17th Rabi-ul-Awwal jo keh Rasool-e-Khuda (s) ki wilaadat ka din hai, Us din ke makhsoos amaal ke liye Shaikh Mufid, Shaikh Shahid aur Sayyed Ibne Tawus ne is tarah bayaan farmaya hai. Jab is roz (17th Rabbi ul Awwal) Madina Munawwara ke alaawa kisi aur maqaam se Rasool Khuda (s) ki ziyarat karna chaahe to Ghusl karne ke baad mitti waghaira se qabr qabr jaisi shakl banaaye aur us par Rasoolullah ka naam likkhe, phir apne dil ko Aan Hazrat (s) ki taraf mutawajjeh kare aur is tarah padhe…", "UrduDescription": "یہ ۱۷ ربیع الاول عید میلاد النبی ؐکا دن ہے، علامہ مجلسیؒ نے زادالمعاد میں اس دن کے اعمال میں کہا : شیخ مفید ؒ اور سید ابن طاؤسؒ نے فرمایا ہے : جب اس روز مدینۂ منورہ کے علاوہ کسی اور مقام سے رسول اﷲؐ کی زیارت کرنا چاہے تو غسل کرنے کے بعد مٹی وغیرہ سے قبر جیسی شکل بنائے اور اس پر رسول اﷲؐ کا اسم گرامی لکھے‘ پھر اپنے دل کو آنحضرتؐ کی طرف متوجہ کرکے یہ پڑھے۔۔۔", "English": null, "Gujarati": null, "RGujarati": null, "RUrdu": null, "Urdu": null, "RArabic": null, "ArabicText1": null, "ArabicGreenSign1": null, "ArabicRedSign1": null, "ArabicBlueSign1": null, "ArabicText2": null, "ArabicGreenSign2": null, "ArabicRedSign2": null, "ArabicBlueSign2": null, "ArabicText3": null, "ArabicGreenSign3": null, "ArabicRedSign3": null, "Ar